Run a test topos certificate spammer to send test certificates to the network

Usage: topos network spam [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --target-node <TARGET_NODE>
          The target node api endpoint [env: TARGET_NODE=]
  -v, --verbose...
          Defines the verbosity level
      --target-nodes-path <TARGET_NODES_PATH>
          Path to file with list of target nodes [env: TARGET_NODES_PATH=]
      --cert-per-batch <CERT_PER_BATCH>
          The number of certificate emitted per batch [env: CERT_PER_BATCH=] [default: 1]
      --batch-time-interval <BATCH_TIME_INTERVAL>
          Time interval between batches in seconds [env: BATCH_TIME_INTERVAL=] [default: 1]
      --nb-subnets <NB_SUBNETS>
          The number of subnets that are emitter [default: 5]
      --byzantine-threshold <BYZANTINE_THRESHOLD>
          The threshold of byzantine among the subnets between 0. (all correct) and 1. (all byzantine) [default: 0]
      --node-per-cert <NODE_PER_CERT>
          The number of nodes to whom we emit the certificate to broadcast Ideally should work with one node to have the liveness property [default: 1]
      --otlp-agent <OTLP_AGENT>
          Socket of the opentelemetry agent endpoint If not provided open telemetry will not be used [env: TOPOS_OTLP_AGENT=]
      --otlp-service-name <OTLP_SERVICE_NAME>
          Otlp service name If not provided open telemetry will not be used [env: TOPOS_OTLP_SERVICE_NAME=]
  -h, --help
          Print help

